Sentencas: A simple electrolyte model for bilayer ion-conducting membrane used in solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) was developed..
Titulo: A simple bilayer electrolyte model for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The model considers yttria-doped bismuth oxide (YDB) and gadolinia-doped ceria (GDC) as the substrate electrolyte, both coated with a thin layer of yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) on the anode side.
Titulo: A simple bilayer electrolyte model for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Migration of oxygen ions and diffusion of free electrons and electron holes through the bilayer electrolyte form the basis of modeling in this study.
Titulo: A simple bilayer electrolyte model for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Results showed that depositing a very thin layer of YSZ onto the substrate electrolyte in the thickness ratio of 1 to 10,000 could increase the interfacial oxygen partial pressure significantly in the bilayer electrolyte and reduce the penetration of electronic current.
Titulo: A simple bilayer electrolyte model for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The improved interfacial oxygen partial pressure by YSZ coating, higher than the equilibrium partial pressure of Bi/Bi2O3, made bismuth oxide a possible candidate for use in SOFC.
Titulo: A simple bilayer electrolyte model for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: An, important result of the electronic blocking effect with bilayer electrolyte SOFC is to improve the open circuit voltage and thus to enhance the output power density of the cell.
Titulo: A simple bilayer electrolyte model for solid oxide fuel cells
